CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 14, 1956, pg. 22 reads: "Planning Installation Services - Officers of the American Woodmen here are shown as they planned installation services last week at the headquarters of Pittsburgh Camp 3 at 2167 Wylie Avenue. Left to right: Neighbors Josephine Moreland, clerk; Louise Edwards, banker; James Littlejohn, prelate; Dorothy Moore, recorder; John Franklin, watchman; Mary Martin, commander, and E.E. Carrington, vice chairman, board of directors.  Officers not on picture: Eugene Redman, vice commander; A. Samuel, escort; Robert Frieson, sentry; Ethel Owens, auditor, and Rosa Miller, chairman, sick committee. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of officers of the American Woodmen, from left: Josephine Moreland, Louise Edwards, James Littlejohn, Dorothy Moore, John Franklin, Mary Martin, and E.E. Carrington, gathered in office interior of Pittsburgh Camp 3 at 2167 Wylie Avenue
